plot: Lt Cedric Daniels lets it be known he is going to leave the department. McNulty pursues the identity of the Jane Doe found floating in the harbor. A pair of young longshoremen, Frank Sobotka's son Ziggy and nephew Nick, heist a container and sell its contents, digital cameras, to men working for The Greek.—Anonymous

Freamon and Moreland have been put in charge of the of the suffocated women case. They travel to Philadelphia to interview the ship's crew but language proves to be a major barrier. Jimmy continues his own informal investigation into the women's death but his former partners are a few steps ahead of him. Lt. Cedric Daniels has been put in charge of the evidence room but tells Jimmy McNulty he'll soon be retiring. Officer Russell is detailed to Baltimore homicide as liaison with the port police. Major Valchek has to deal with the missing surveillance van. The investigation into Sobotka is leaderless and Valchek confronts acting Commissioner Burell. Under orders from Avon Barksdale, Stringer Bell Bell sets up the prison guard whose been causing him grief. Nick Sobotka is under financial pressure so he and his cousin Ziggy hijack a truckload of electronics which they sell to the Greek.—garykmcd

Concerned over how to provide for his girlfriend and their daughter, Sobotka's nephew Nick (Pablo Schreiber) reluctantly joins his errant cousin Ziggy (James Ransone) in stealing containers for the Greeks. Having returned to Baltimore, Omar recruits an unusual new crew. Bunk and Freamon are assigned the Jane Does, assisted by Russell. Meanwhile, having spoken to Prez, Valchek realises Burrell has assigned humps to his Sobotka detail, and threatens to disrupt Burrell's campaign for promotion unless a new detail is assembled. In prison, Avon goes to extreme measures to deal with a CO who is hassling Wee-Bey and selling drugs to inmates.—Bertaut
